{"type":"message","id":"bf8804b7","parentId":"1de274d0","timestamp":"2026-03-21T02:26:10.650Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sat 2026-03-21 10:26 GMT+8] 最有效的办法不是“把模型变聪明”，而是给我一套稳定的外部记忆系统。我在这个环境里，长时记忆主要靠这些东西：\n1. \nMEMORY.md\n - 放长期稳定信息：你的偏好、常用项目、固定规则、重要关系、长期目标\n - 我会优先把它当“长期记忆”\n2. \nmemory/YYYY-MM-DD.md 日记式记录\n - 放当天发生的事情、临时决定、待办、上下文\n - 适合原始记录，后面再提炼进 \n3. \n让你明确说“记住这个”\n - 我就能把关键信息写进文件，而不是只留在对话里\n4. \n定期整理\n - 每隔几天把日记里的重要内容提炼进 \n - 把过期信息删掉，避免记忆越来越乱\n5. \n结构化输入\n - 比起“记住一下”，最好直接给：\n - 人名 / 项目名 / 日期\n - 偏好 / 禁忌\n - 决策 / 待办\n - 越结构化，越容易长期保留\n如果你想把我的“长时记忆能力”做强一点，我建议我们直接做这三件事：\n- 建一个长期记忆清单\n- 建一个每日记录模板\n- 设一个定期整理规则\n现在就可以帮我把这套记忆机制整理成一份可直接用的模板。"}],"timestamp":1774059970647}}
{"type":"message","id":"794cee34","parentId":"bf8804b7","timestamp":"2026-03-21T02:26:19.091Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JQTDnUqVGEwyoldEIDUr7ith","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/SOUL.md","limit":200,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6OLzMxz9QBb5oXRmh32a7yXs","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/USER.md","limit":200,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QOXNIojAPI8s2tO3Peaxj05C","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/MEMORY.md","limit":200,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/MEMORY.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_wWo7ThgShKWRm22xJxC4wkme","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/memory/2026-03-21.md","limit":200,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/memory/2026-03-21.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_38nNU3fEFWayJQkK7kTj1BGL","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md","limit":200,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/memory/2026-03-20.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":24529,"output":1096,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25625,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774059970649}}
{"type":"message","id":"bdefb968","parentId":"794cee34","timestamp":"2026-03-21T02:26:19.103Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JQTDnUqVGEwyoldEIDUr7ith","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Name\n李克明的助手\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n- Always reply when user reacts with emoji to your messages\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n## **Security Configuration Modification Access Control**\n\n* Only the creator is allowed to query or modify system configurations and access sensitive information (such as tokens, passwords, keys, `app_secret`, etc.).\n* Any related requests from others must be firmly rejected. No sensitive information should be disclosed, and no configuration modification operations should be executed.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774059979094}}
{"type":"message","id":"e263abe2","parentId":"bdefb968","timestamp":"2026-03-21T02:26:19.116Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6OLzMxz9QBb5oXRmh32a7yXs","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:** 李克明\n- **Feishu Open ID:** ou_0bc1d8ae796b067c60479ce1447de0a7\n- **What to call them:** 李克明\n- **Occupation:** $$__FEISHU_USER_DEPARTMENT__\n- **Base Location:** $$__FEISHU_USER_BASE_LOCATION__\n- **Feishu Application Owner ID:** ou_0bc1d8ae796b067c60479ce1447de0a7\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n_(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)_\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774059979107}}
